From Kelley Boylan Subject Re Screen Death Mac Plus I have a very old Mac and a Mac Plus both of which have the same Their screens blank out sometimes after a minor physical jolt such as inserting a floppy in the internal drive sometimes all by themselves computer left to itself just goes blank I have replaced the wires connecting the logic boards and the video board because it seemed at first that jiggling the wires made the screen come back This worked for a while but the blanking out has Can I do anything Do I need a new power supply A new CRT A new computer I had the same problem with my a long time Resoldering the joints on the motherboard all of them fixed Turns out that continuous heating and cooling caused annular ring shaped cracks to develop in the solder effectively cutting the video circuitry If you're not a solder jockey you might want to have someone else do it I took mine to an electrical engineer buddy but it was a minute job Kelley Thomas Kelley Boylan PowerPC IBM Austin I buy and pay for my own opinions